  "notes": [
    "No public OpenAPI spec exists. /api_internal/, /ember/openapi.json, etc. all return 404. The single 403 was /ember/workflows.json which suggests a real route guarded by tighter auth.",
    "Auth is cookie session + X-CSRF-Token. Token is in <meta name=csrf-token>. Refreshes automatically on each page load. credentials:'include' attaches all cookies.",
    "OPTIONS preflight returns 404 \u2014 same-origin requests, so no CORS preflight required. Just send the POST/PUT/PATCH directly.",
    "Most endpoints follow Ember Data adapter conventions: GET / POST /collection, GET / PUT / DELETE /collection/{id}. The app uses custom adapters so some endpoints have non-Ember shapes (e.g. /ember/operator_workflows/get_live_fin_workflows_count).",
    "Predicate group format is consistent across rules, views, escalations, content segments, and ruleset audience filters. Same JSON shape works everywhere predicates are accepted.",
    "Workflows = matching_system/rulesets + ruleset_links to a triggerable-custom-bot object. The visual builder graph lives in object.visual_builder_object.groups[].steps[].",
    "Inbox views are stored under inbox_folders. Creating a new filtered view = POST to inbox_folders or a sibling 'views' endpoint with a view_summary block (creation endpoint not yet probed but the read shape is fully captured).",
